1
00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:35,040
=Love Again=

2
00:01:35,330 --> 00:01:38,140
=Episode 17=

3
00:01:38,340 --> 00:01:38,810
What?

4
00:01:39,420 --> 00:01:41,419
Ms. Nie wasn't willing
to see my father-in-law, huh?

5
00:01:41,420 --> 00:01:42,450
That's right.

6
00:01:43,900 --> 00:01:44,220
However,

7
00:01:44,570 --> 00:01:47,450
Ms. Nie was pretty courteous to me

8
00:01:47,530 --> 00:01:48,570
and Ms. Peng.

9
00:01:48,860 --> 00:01:50,090
But we were pretty sensible.

10
00:01:50,980 --> 00:01:53,010
We said we were heading out
to buy some stuff.

11
00:01:53,060 --> 00:01:54,500
We gave them time to speak

12
00:01:54,700 --> 00:01:55,500
in private.

13
00:01:56,290 --> 00:01:57,730
But your father-in-law came out

14
00:01:57,730 --> 00:01:58,800
before we went downstairs.

15
00:01:58,930 --> 00:02:00,230
I was calling him from the back.

16
00:02:00,290 --> 00:02:02,980
I called him multiple times.

17
00:02:03,570 --> 00:02:04,340
He didn't hear me.

18
00:02:06,530 --> 00:02:07,320
He was distracted.

19
00:02:09,060 --> 00:02:09,420
Mom,

20
00:02:10,140 --> 00:02:12,930
how was Ms. Nie's condition
when you guys went there?

21
00:02:13,970 --> 00:02:16,060
The caretaker thought
she was doing well.

22
00:02:16,060 --> 00:02:17,680
She said she took half a bowl of congee.

23
00:02:17,740 --> 00:02:19,220
I don't think she was doing well.

24
00:02:19,810 --> 00:02:21,250
She was so pale.

25
00:02:21,580 --> 00:02:22,930
She looked like a vampire.

26
00:02:24,650 --> 00:02:25,410
I think

27
00:02:25,740 --> 00:02:27,530
she didn't want Dad
to see her in that state.

28
00:02:30,620 --> 00:02:31,750
When is her son coming back?

29
00:02:32,740 --> 00:02:33,340
In two days.

30
00:02:33,740 --> 00:02:34,780
In two days?

31
00:02:35,460 --> 00:02:36,060
My goodness.

32
00:02:37,530 --> 00:02:38,250
This is...

33
00:02:39,780 --> 00:02:40,660
Let me answer a call.

34
00:02:48,020 --> 00:02:48,370
Jin.

35
00:02:48,370 --> 00:02:48,900
Mr. Shen.

36
00:02:48,970 --> 00:02:49,689
What's the matter?

37
00:02:49,690 --> 00:02:50,370
It's like this.

38
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:51,639
By the way,

39
00:02:51,640 --> 00:02:54,340
you have to tell Shen Qing about this.

40
00:02:54,810 --> 00:02:56,130
He should stop jogging like that.

41
00:02:56,460 --> 00:02:58,090
Working overtime
is already a huge burden

42
00:02:58,090 --> 00:02:58,970
to his body.

43
00:02:59,130 --> 00:03:00,950
He might die if he does
long-distance jogging.

44
00:03:01,100 --> 00:03:02,399
If something does happen to him,

45
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:04,020
no one can rescue him.

46
00:03:04,340 --> 00:03:04,810
Mr. Shen.

47
00:03:05,780 --> 00:03:06,220
Mr. Shen?

48
00:03:06,500 --> 00:03:07,300
Is that okay?

49
00:03:07,410 --> 00:03:10,410
Alright. Send it to Mr. An.

50
00:03:10,530 --> 00:03:11,130
Alright.

51
00:03:11,440 --> 00:03:12,639
I'll send it to Mr. An, then.

52
00:03:12,640 --> 00:03:13,060
Okay.

53
00:03:14,970 --> 00:03:15,650
As humans,

54
00:03:16,530 --> 00:03:18,180
we need to look after our bodies.

55
00:03:19,020 --> 00:03:20,650
Just look at Ms. Nie.

56
00:03:21,250 --> 00:03:22,930
She was so pitiful.

57
00:03:26,060 --> 00:03:28,530
You get yourself a partner

58
00:03:28,530 --> 00:03:30,180
to enjoy your later years in life,

59
00:03:30,220 --> 00:03:32,220
not to look after you
and see you off one last time.

60
00:03:35,340 --> 00:03:36,410
That's about it.

61
00:03:37,220 --> 00:03:37,910
Don't you agree?

62
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:40,680
His wife just passed away. And now,
he's facing a similar situation.

63
00:03:41,340 --> 00:03:44,180
Who could withstand such an event?

64
00:03:44,740 --> 00:03:46,500
Lower your volume. Stop saying that.

65
00:03:48,970 --> 00:03:50,810
What's wrong? Did I say something wrong?

66
00:03:52,850 --> 00:03:54,650
Fine. I'll stop here.

67
00:03:54,900 --> 00:03:56,130
I need to head back now.

68
00:03:56,580 --> 00:03:57,800
I have to cook for your father.

69
00:03:57,800 --> 00:03:59,409
I've been visiting the hospital too much

70
00:03:59,410 --> 00:04:01,800
that I didn't have time
to look after your father.

71
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:02,649
It must've been tough.

72
00:04:02,650 --> 00:04:03,780
Alright. I'll be going now.

73
00:04:03,870 --> 00:04:04,529
You can go ahead.

74
00:04:04,530 --> 00:04:05,770
I'll stop telling him about it.

75
00:04:06,060 --> 00:04:06,370
Okay.

76
00:04:06,740 --> 00:04:07,500
Stop seeing me off.

77
00:04:07,900 --> 00:04:09,870
You guys have to cook as well.
I'll make a move now.

78
00:04:13,250 --> 00:04:14,060
Mom, take care.

79
00:04:14,530 --> 00:04:15,250
Alright.

80
00:04:20,440 --> 00:04:22,139
How could you
not bid farewell to my mother

81
00:04:22,140 --> 00:04:23,020
when she was leaving?

82
00:04:24,380 --> 00:04:26,510
Can you ask your mother
to think before she speaks?

83
00:04:26,510 --> 00:04:28,899
What does she mean by
my father is facing a similar situation?

84
00:04:28,900 --> 00:04:29,950
That's terrible, you know?

85
00:04:31,610 --> 00:04:33,220
My mother has the right to say anything.

86
00:04:33,700 --> 00:04:36,090
When your mother was sick,
my mother took care of her.

87
00:04:36,340 --> 00:04:38,780
This time, my mother was the one
who rescued Ms. Nie as well.

88
00:04:39,200 --> 00:04:40,849
If my mother actually
gave it some thought,

89
00:04:40,850 --> 00:04:42,650
she would never come to the Shen family

90
00:04:42,940 --> 00:04:44,049
and work as a free labor.

91
00:04:44,050 --> 00:04:45,490
So what if she said that?

92
00:04:48,290 --> 00:04:49,140
Where are you going?

93
00:04:49,260 --> 00:04:50,140
I'm going to jog.

94
00:04:50,380 --> 00:04:52,220
You shouldn't just jog
when I criticize you.

95
00:04:52,220 --> 00:04:53,220
Even my mother knows

96
00:04:53,220 --> 00:04:55,530
working 9-9-6 and jogging
can easily lead to sudden death.

97
00:04:57,900 --> 00:04:59,250
I'll stop, then. Are you happy now?

98
00:05:11,700 --> 00:05:13,340
I know you're worried about your father.

99
00:05:14,090 --> 00:05:15,700
You think I'm not worried about him?

100
00:05:20,900 --> 00:05:23,380
But love is fragile in the face

101
00:05:24,730 --> 00:05:25,290
of reality.

102
00:05:35,610 --> 00:05:36,090
Dad.

103
00:05:37,940 --> 00:05:38,340
Dad?

104
00:05:46,490 --> 00:05:47,260
You're here, huh?

105
00:05:47,780 --> 00:05:49,290
Dad, where did you go?

106
00:05:49,290 --> 00:05:50,260
It's so windy outside.

107
00:05:50,490 --> 00:05:51,700
I went to the market.

108
00:05:53,650 --> 00:05:55,020
I bought some chrysanthemum greens.

109
00:05:55,260 --> 00:05:57,490
Ms. Nie likes lighter food.

110
00:06:03,580 --> 00:06:04,020
Dad,

111
00:06:04,900 --> 00:06:06,380
you should take some medicine.

112
00:06:06,820 --> 00:06:07,090
Okay.

113
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:09,769
You want to make chrysanthemum
greens soup with egg, right?

114
00:06:09,770 --> 00:06:10,530
I'll make it.

115
00:06:17,730 --> 00:06:18,490
It's fine.

116
00:06:18,770 --> 00:06:19,989
This is a simple soup to make.

117
00:06:19,990 --> 00:06:20,940
I can make it myself.

118
00:06:24,290 --> 00:06:24,700
Dad,

119
00:06:26,260 --> 00:06:27,290
didn't Ms. Nie say

120
00:06:27,410 --> 00:06:29,470
that she didn't want you
to visit her at the hospital?

121
00:06:31,610 --> 00:06:32,380
I have to visit her.

122
00:06:35,580 --> 00:06:36,410
If I don't go now,

123
00:06:36,970 --> 00:06:37,700
then when?

124
00:06:44,490 --> 00:06:45,580
I have a cough.

125
00:06:46,340 --> 00:06:47,460
I won't enter her ward.

126
00:07:09,650 --> 00:07:10,380
Professor Shen?

127
00:07:11,050 --> 00:07:12,220
What are you doing here?

128
00:07:12,410 --> 00:07:13,649
Aren't you entering her ward?

129
00:07:13,650 --> 00:07:13,970
I...

130
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:15,339
I was planning to head there.

131
00:07:15,340 --> 00:07:16,340
But I have a cough.

132
00:07:19,340 --> 00:07:20,260
I'm afraid that I might

133
00:07:20,850 --> 00:07:22,020
infect her.

134
00:07:23,020 --> 00:07:23,900
Great timing.

135
00:07:24,850 --> 00:07:25,170
So,

136
00:07:25,610 --> 00:07:28,050
please deliver this soup
to her on my behalf.

137
00:07:28,610 --> 00:07:31,460
I made this chrysanthemum
greens soup with egg. It's light.

138
00:07:31,780 --> 00:07:32,900
Did you make it yourself?

139
00:07:33,140 --> 00:07:33,900
That's right.

140
00:07:35,940 --> 00:07:37,780
Look. There's one more thing inside.

141
00:07:38,260 --> 00:07:39,410
There's a radio.

142
00:07:41,970 --> 00:07:43,710
That's quite a serious cough
you have there.

143
00:07:44,340 --> 00:07:44,850
I'm fine.

144
00:07:52,900 --> 00:07:53,460
And this.

145
00:07:54,290 --> 00:07:55,090
For this radio,

146
00:07:56,220 --> 00:07:57,560
there’s an opera channel in there.

147
00:07:58,340 --> 00:07:59,970
I've downloaded some
to the memory card.

148
00:08:01,290 --> 00:08:03,120
Tell her that I've downloaded
some opera songs.

149
00:08:03,460 --> 00:08:05,070
She can listen to them
when she likes it.

150
00:08:07,140 --> 00:08:07,460
You...

151
00:08:07,610 --> 00:08:08,360
Please help me out.

152
00:08:09,490 --> 00:08:10,340
You're so thoughtful.

153
00:08:13,340 --> 00:08:13,850
If so,

154
00:08:14,460 --> 00:08:15,339
sorry for the trouble.

155
00:08:15,340 --> 00:08:16,620
I'll surely deliver them to her.

156
00:08:19,610 --> 00:08:20,040
By the way,

157
00:08:22,530 --> 00:08:23,090
Peng,

158
00:08:26,260 --> 00:08:27,850
don't tell her that I was here.

159
00:08:28,610 --> 00:08:29,610
Just say

160
00:08:30,490 --> 00:08:32,000
that you brought these things for her.

161
00:08:35,140 --> 00:08:36,380
I'll entrust this task to you.

162
00:08:39,890 --> 00:08:40,460
Please go now.

163
00:08:40,580 --> 00:08:40,890
Okay.

164
00:08:48,490 --> 00:08:49,180
Ms. Nie,

165
00:08:49,940 --> 00:08:51,890
Professor Shen made this for you.

166
00:08:52,490 --> 00:08:54,060
I made this for you.

167
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:57,420
He was afraid that he might
infect you with his cough.

168
00:08:57,770 --> 00:08:59,660
That's why he told me
to deliver this to you.

169
00:09:00,340 --> 00:09:02,130
He even wanted me
to send his regards to you.

170
00:09:04,180 --> 00:09:05,220
You have two sets of soup

171
00:09:05,850 --> 00:09:06,870
that are filled with love.

172
00:09:07,580 --> 00:09:10,060
Ms. Nie, you're amazing.

173
00:09:12,940 --> 00:09:13,920
Thank you guys so much.

174
00:09:14,820 --> 00:09:17,060
Was Professor Shen's cough serious?

175
00:09:18,420 --> 00:09:19,660
I think he caught a cold.

176
00:09:19,890 --> 00:09:20,610
It's not that bad.

177
00:09:22,850 --> 00:09:23,330
By the way,

178
00:09:23,490 --> 00:09:24,300
there's this as well.

179
00:09:25,130 --> 00:09:26,840
Professor Shen told me
to hand this to you.

180
00:09:26,850 --> 00:09:29,610
He said he recorded your favorite songs.

181
00:10:08,090 --> 00:10:09,370
You mustn't get off the bed.

182
00:10:11,220 --> 00:10:11,820
It's fine.

183
00:10:18,180 --> 00:10:18,610
Slowly.

184
00:10:50,610 --> 00:10:51,300
Was it nice?

185
00:10:55,850 --> 00:10:56,540
Yeah.

186
00:11:33,580 --> 00:11:34,250
Ms. Nie.

187
00:11:35,490 --> 00:11:37,660
Ms. Nie, your son is calling you.

188
00:11:38,660 --> 00:11:39,610
Your son is calling you.

189
00:11:47,090 --> 00:11:47,490
Hello?

190
00:11:48,010 --> 00:11:49,730
Hello, Mom?
I have something to tell you.

191
00:11:49,970 --> 00:11:50,490
What is it?

192
00:11:50,850 --> 00:11:52,060
Ru will give birth soon.

193
00:11:52,180 --> 00:11:52,500
What?

194
00:11:52,500 --> 00:11:54,509
Her delivery is two days earlier
than the due date.

195
00:11:54,510 --> 00:11:55,940
Ru is going to give birth?

196
00:11:56,660 --> 00:11:57,240
That's right.

197
00:11:57,300 --> 00:11:59,930
I plan to change into sterile clothing
and keep her company inside.

198
00:12:01,820 --> 00:12:02,610
Mom, I'm sorry.

199
00:12:02,970 --> 00:12:04,460
I won't be flying there tonight.

200
00:12:04,500 --> 00:12:06,239
I've changed my flight
to tomorrow afternoon.

201
00:12:06,240 --> 00:12:07,420
It's fine.

202
00:12:08,490 --> 00:12:10,060
You don't need to rush back here.

203
00:12:10,970 --> 00:12:13,300
At this moment,
you should keep Ru company.

204
00:12:14,660 --> 00:12:15,610
I've gotten much better.

205
00:12:16,460 --> 00:12:17,800
My condition has been stabilized.

206
00:12:18,220 --> 00:12:19,850
And, Ms. Wang took great care of me.

207
00:12:19,850 --> 00:12:20,730
Don't worry about it.

208
00:12:21,180 --> 00:12:21,820
Mom, I...

209
00:12:21,820 --> 00:12:24,060
Son, listen to me.

210
00:12:25,610 --> 00:12:26,010
Love is

211
00:12:27,300 --> 00:12:29,220
passed down from the top.

212
00:12:30,850 --> 00:12:32,060
I'm old now.

213
00:12:34,370 --> 00:12:36,070
But your child
is just born into the world.

214
00:12:37,300 --> 00:12:38,090
At this moment,

215
00:12:38,890 --> 00:12:40,770
you have to look after Ru

216
00:12:41,890 --> 00:12:43,250
and witness the moment

217
00:12:44,460 --> 00:12:45,910
as a new life is born into the world.

218
00:12:46,340 --> 00:12:46,770
Okay.

219
00:12:47,300 --> 00:12:48,460
Mom, I'll head inside first.

220
00:13:31,970 --> 00:13:33,090
Am I wrong?

221
00:13:35,460 --> 00:13:38,220
Love is actually strong
in the face of reality.

222
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:49,060
(Healthy lotus seeds and red bean soup)
Lotus seeds.

223
00:13:49,340 --> 00:13:50,970
How much should I put?

224
00:13:51,770 --> 00:13:52,420
My goodness.

225
00:13:53,490 --> 00:13:54,690
She's inferior to the matron.

226
00:13:57,010 --> 00:13:58,940
The matron took care of
the entire family herself.

227
00:13:59,730 --> 00:14:00,540
But Ms. Nie?

228
00:14:01,410 --> 00:14:03,180
Her entire family
took care of her instead.

229
00:14:04,340 --> 00:14:06,340
She’s having a cancer relapse.

230
00:14:07,540 --> 00:14:08,300
My goodness.

231
00:14:08,610 --> 00:14:10,820
Peng Yulan is considered her love rival.

232
00:14:11,370 --> 00:14:13,250
Even so, she's looking after her.

233
00:14:13,540 --> 00:14:15,220
You keep comparing them.

234
00:14:16,220 --> 00:14:17,580
What's the point?

235
00:14:18,580 --> 00:14:19,730
I was just stating facts.

236
00:14:21,060 --> 00:14:22,490
And, I'm only telling you about it.

237
00:14:28,490 --> 00:14:28,940
Hello?

238
00:14:29,490 --> 00:14:30,130
Peng Yulan.

239
00:14:30,660 --> 00:14:31,420
Baoqin.

240
00:14:32,300 --> 00:14:34,090
Ms. Nie just got herself a grandson.

241
00:14:35,850 --> 00:14:37,800
She didn't want her son
to come back and visit her.

242
00:14:40,730 --> 00:14:42,940
Isn't that like forgetting your mother
after having a son?

243
00:14:46,060 --> 00:14:47,610
That's ridiculous!

244
00:14:49,610 --> 00:14:50,470
His son was just born.

245
00:14:50,490 --> 00:14:52,730
He can keep his child
company for the rest of his life.

246
00:14:52,890 --> 00:14:56,300
But her mother
is suffering from a cancer relapse.

247
00:14:56,300 --> 00:14:57,820
How long can he keep her company?

248
00:14:58,660 --> 00:15:00,890
Am I right? How many times
can he come back and visit her?

249
00:15:02,620 --> 00:15:04,890
Does he intend to come back
during her memorial service?

250
00:15:05,610 --> 00:15:08,730
I said it already! One shouldn't
send their children abroad.

251
00:15:08,760 --> 00:15:10,539
Once you do it,
your child is no longer yours.

252
00:15:10,540 --> 00:15:11,670
They'll turn into ingrates.

253
00:15:12,700 --> 00:15:13,700
You guys...

254
00:15:14,490 --> 00:15:16,730
Mom, calm down. Talk nicely.

255
00:15:17,580 --> 00:15:19,090
Fine. I'll calm down.

256
00:15:19,820 --> 00:15:21,490
I'll talk nicely. Got it.

257
00:15:24,060 --> 00:15:24,700
In-law.

258
00:15:25,370 --> 00:15:26,540
If her son doesn't come back,

259
00:15:27,340 --> 00:15:28,610
what does Ms. Nie intend

260
00:15:29,340 --> 00:15:30,370
to do with her condition?

261
00:15:32,940 --> 00:15:33,890
Ms. Wang said

262
00:15:34,820 --> 00:15:36,250
she had chosen conservative therapy.

263
00:15:38,180 --> 00:15:38,790
Conservative...

264
00:15:39,810 --> 00:15:40,700
By the way, Shen Qing,

265
00:15:40,700 --> 00:15:43,300
did you show her X-ray film
to the experts at the cancer hospital?

266
00:15:43,300 --> 00:15:44,130
What did they say?

267
00:15:44,250 --> 00:15:44,660
Yeah.

268
00:15:45,820 --> 00:15:47,130
There's no better solution.

269
00:15:49,850 --> 00:15:52,180
Even so, we can't just leave
Ms. Nie in the hospital

270
00:15:52,180 --> 00:15:53,760
and let the caretaker take care of her.

271
00:15:55,420 --> 00:15:55,770
Dad,

272
00:15:56,340 --> 00:15:58,610
does Ms. Nie have any other relatives
in the country?

273
00:16:00,890 --> 00:16:01,220
No.

274
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:05,770
Why don't I deliver meals
to Ms. Nie every day?

275
00:16:07,770 --> 00:16:08,180
You?

276
00:16:09,010 --> 00:16:09,440
Will you...

277
00:16:10,730 --> 00:16:11,610
Who'll cook?

278
00:16:13,490 --> 00:16:13,850
I...

279
00:16:14,540 --> 00:16:14,890
I...

