00:29:07,290 --> 00:29:08,970
Ms. Nie lives alone.

565
00:29:09,010 --> 00:29:11,010
I can understand
if she's moving to a nursing home.

566
00:29:11,380 --> 00:29:13,010
But you have children and grandchildren.

567
00:29:13,490 --> 00:29:15,000
Why are you moving to a nursing home?

568
00:29:15,290 --> 00:29:16,140
I don't agree with it.

569
00:29:17,770 --> 00:29:19,860
A few years back,
when your mother was sick,

570
00:29:20,330 --> 00:29:23,420
you, Lina, and Lina's parents

571
00:29:23,970 --> 00:29:25,220
had made huge sacrifices.

572
00:29:25,700 --> 00:29:26,380
All these years,

573
00:29:27,220 --> 00:29:28,180
this family of ours

574
00:29:28,620 --> 00:29:29,620
had been a blissful one.

575
00:29:30,290 --> 00:29:32,769
If so, why are you moving to a nursing home?

576
00:29:32,770 --> 00:29:34,730
Why would someone blissful
move to a nursing home?

577
00:29:34,810 --> 00:29:36,290
What should we do about Ms. Nie, then?

578
00:29:37,380 --> 00:29:39,330
She can no longer live alone.

579
00:29:40,380 --> 00:29:42,460
I've been to all those nursing homes.

580
00:29:42,660 --> 00:29:43,890
I've made my inquiries as well.

581
00:29:43,900 --> 00:29:45,809
The nursing homes
have great living conditions.

582
00:29:45,810 --> 00:29:47,390
They even have professional caretakers.

583
00:29:48,490 --> 00:29:49,570
This is what I think.

584
00:29:50,380 --> 00:29:52,100
You see, you're busy with work.

585
00:29:52,810 --> 00:29:54,180
Duole is growing up as well.

586
00:29:54,770 --> 00:29:55,830
If I move to a nursing home

587
00:29:56,100 --> 00:29:57,380
and take care of Ms. Nie,

588
00:29:57,570 --> 00:29:59,049
there will be more time for everyone.

589
00:29:59,050 --> 00:30:01,010
Lina can even do the things she likes.

590
00:30:01,010 --> 00:30:01,480
Am I right?

591
00:30:01,730 --> 00:30:03,490
Dad, stop using me as an excuse.

592
00:30:03,810 --> 00:30:06,830
No matter how good the living conditions
are, it's not as good as our family's.

593
00:30:07,570 --> 00:30:09,530
I know you want to spend
more time with Ms. Nie.

594
00:30:10,660 --> 00:30:12,170
If so, we can think of other solutions.

595
00:30:13,970 --> 00:30:14,330
Dad,

596
00:30:14,810 --> 00:30:15,810
what about this?

597
00:30:16,220 --> 00:30:18,050
If you insist on moving
to a nursing home,

598
00:30:18,140 --> 00:30:19,700
can we find one
that's near to our house?

599
00:30:20,380 --> 00:30:20,900
I can

600
00:30:21,250 --> 00:30:22,660
send you there when I go to work

601
00:30:22,940 --> 00:30:24,010
and pick you up after work.

602
00:30:24,460 --> 00:30:25,010
Is that okay?

603
00:30:25,570 --> 00:30:26,620
But you never get off work.

604
00:30:26,810 --> 00:30:28,460
Even so, you're still around, right?

605
00:30:30,050 --> 00:30:31,490
In the end, I still have to do it.

606
00:30:31,860 --> 00:30:32,870
I have to do everything.

607
00:30:34,740 --> 00:30:36,100
I spoke up for you when my mother

608
00:30:36,120 --> 00:30:37,429
felt sorry for me, you know?

609
00:30:37,430 --> 00:30:39,899
After all this time, you never stopped
to consider my feelings.

610
00:30:39,900 --> 00:30:40,770
Wait. Lina, you...

611
00:30:41,180 --> 00:30:41,420
You...

612
00:30:43,810 --> 00:30:44,140
Look.

613
00:30:44,900 --> 00:30:46,250
You two are arguing

614
00:30:46,290 --> 00:30:47,729
because of this point again, right?

615
00:30:47,730 --> 00:30:49,640
You guys got into a conflict
because of me again.

616
00:30:52,420 --> 00:30:54,180
If I move to a nursing home now,

617
00:30:55,290 --> 00:30:56,530
you guys will have more time,

618
00:30:56,730 --> 00:30:58,810
and you guys won't
need to worry about me.

619
00:30:58,900 --> 00:31:00,900
This way, you guys
wouldn't need to argue.

620
00:31:01,010 --> 00:31:02,380
Dad, I'm your son.

621
00:31:02,380 --> 00:31:04,330
Who else should I be worried about?

622
00:31:04,660 --> 00:31:06,290
You can show concern to Ms. Nie,

623
00:31:06,420 --> 00:31:07,490
write to her,

624
00:31:07,490 --> 00:31:08,770
or visit her anytime you like.

625
00:31:08,970 --> 00:31:09,630
But why must you

626
00:31:09,770 --> 00:31:11,380
move to a nursing home
together with her?

627
00:31:11,490 --> 00:31:13,060
Can't you spare a little thought for me?

628
00:31:14,180 --> 00:31:15,970
What are you saying?

629
00:31:15,970 --> 00:31:17,530
How am I not sparing a thought for you?

630
00:31:18,900 --> 00:31:19,490
Enough.

631
00:31:20,860 --> 00:31:22,530
Anyway, I'm just here
to notify you guys.

632
00:31:23,620 --> 00:31:23,900
No.

633
00:31:23,970 --> 00:31:25,530
I've already made up my mind. That's it.

634
00:31:26,140 --> 00:31:26,380
But...

635
00:31:27,490 --> 00:31:27,940
Dad,

636
00:31:28,290 --> 00:31:28,620
you...

637
00:31:29,730 --> 00:31:30,050
This...

638
00:31:33,860 --> 00:31:34,620
What should we do?

639
00:31:34,970 --> 00:31:36,290
How should I know?

640
00:31:36,380 --> 00:31:37,160
What should we do?

641
00:31:39,250 --> 00:31:40,380
Mom is right.

642
00:31:40,770 --> 00:31:41,330
Your father

643
00:31:41,330 --> 00:31:43,810
is there to provide for
Ms. Nie's care in her last few years.

644
00:31:45,050 --> 00:31:46,620
How can we not worry about him?

645
00:31:46,770 --> 00:31:47,700
Our entire family

646
00:31:47,700 --> 00:31:48,940
had to take care of her

647
00:31:48,940 --> 00:31:50,150
when Ms. Nie was hospitalized.

648
00:31:50,660 --> 00:31:51,620
You should stop.

649
00:31:51,860 --> 00:31:53,650
You're behaving more and more
like your mother.

650
00:31:54,730 --> 00:31:55,870
What's wrong with my mother?

651
00:31:55,960 --> 00:31:58,009
My mother delivered meals
to your mother in hospital.

652
00:31:58,010 --> 00:31:59,420
She did the same for your father.

653
00:31:59,420 --> 00:32:01,100
She even did the same for Ms. Nie.

654
00:32:01,100 --> 00:32:02,180
Did my mother offend you?

655
00:32:04,460 --> 00:32:06,049
The Shen family is full of hypocrites.

656
00:32:06,050 --> 00:32:08,720
You guys adopt realism on the one hand
and criticize it on the other.

657
00:32:10,100 --> 00:32:10,660
Talk to me.

658
00:32:10,970 --> 00:32:12,070
Why are you keeping quiet?

659
00:32:14,970 --> 00:32:15,770
Where are you going?

660
00:32:16,330 --> 00:32:17,000
I'm going to jog.

661
00:32:18,600 --> 00:32:21,020
He always goes jogging
when the situation isn't in his favor.

662
00:32:21,180 --> 00:32:22,740
Don't come back if you're that capable.

663
00:32:26,140 --> 00:32:27,060
Here. Have some water.

664
00:32:27,100 --> 00:32:27,660
It's fine.

665
00:32:28,380 --> 00:32:28,910
Who's there?

666
00:32:31,970 --> 00:32:32,810
Lina texted me.

667
00:32:33,035 --> 00:32:36,179
(Lina: My father-in-law said he wanted
to move to a nursing home with Ms. Nie.)

668
00:32:36,180 --> 00:32:38,860
She said my in-law
wanted to move to a nursing home

669
00:32:39,330 --> 00:32:40,460
with Ms. Nie.

670
00:32:41,570 --> 00:32:42,280
What should we do?

671
00:32:42,700 --> 00:32:43,770
I don't know.

672
00:32:46,010 --> 00:32:47,620
Is he sick in the head?

673
00:32:48,380 --> 00:32:50,690
He doesn't want to live in his own house
with his children.

674
00:32:51,290 --> 00:32:53,370
He wants to waste his money
on a nursing home instead.

675
00:32:53,490 --> 00:32:54,660
What is he thinking?

676
00:32:55,250 --> 00:32:55,970
My goodness.

677
00:32:58,180 --> 00:32:59,770
Are all men sick in the head?

678
00:33:01,180 --> 00:33:03,140
Why am I involved now? Geez.

679
00:33:03,620 --> 00:33:04,110
My goodness.

680
00:33:04,810 --> 00:33:05,780
How dare you talk back...

681
00:33:06,140 --> 00:33:07,530
You should stop arguing.

682
00:33:12,180 --> 00:33:15,730
Say, why do you think he wants
to live in a nursing home?

683
00:33:15,970 --> 00:33:17,000
What about his treatment?

684
00:33:17,860 --> 00:33:19,330
I have no idea.

685
00:33:21,420 --> 00:33:22,010
Peng Yulan.

686
00:33:22,770 --> 00:33:23,940
I think my in-law

687
00:33:23,940 --> 00:33:25,620
is still a loyal person
with deep feelings.

688
00:33:26,940 --> 00:33:27,920
You should wait for him.

689
00:33:28,140 --> 00:33:28,760
It's worth it.

690
00:33:31,290 --> 00:33:33,250
Sweet talk means nothing.

691
00:33:33,660 --> 00:33:35,660
This is what you call true love.

692
00:33:38,730 --> 00:33:39,810
Baoqin, say,

693
00:33:40,810 --> 00:33:42,100
in this life,

694
00:33:42,490 --> 00:33:43,050
do you think

695
00:33:43,530 --> 00:33:45,380
we've experienced true love before?

696
00:33:47,730 --> 00:33:48,530
True love, huh?

697
00:33:52,860 --> 00:33:53,660
Look at Liu.

698
00:33:55,620 --> 00:33:56,290
I...

699
00:33:56,770 --> 00:33:58,940
Although our love isn't anything flashy,

700
00:33:59,290 --> 00:33:59,860
I...

701
00:34:00,530 --> 00:34:02,570
Anyway, if he doesn't
return home tonight,

702
00:34:03,010 --> 00:34:04,900
I won't be able to sleep.

703
00:34:06,220 --> 00:34:07,810
Is that love?

704
00:34:08,620 --> 00:34:09,700
Or is that just a habit?

705
00:34:10,860 --> 00:34:12,970
When a habit becomes second nature,
that's love.

706
00:34:15,980 --> 00:34:17,320
Peng Yulan, you're something else.

707
00:34:17,450 --> 00:34:18,800
You're quite fancy with your words.

708
00:34:27,020 --> 00:34:27,470
Excellent!

709
00:34:28,020 --> 00:34:28,450
Excellent!

710
00:34:28,770 --> 00:34:29,540
Drink up!

711
00:34:29,850 --> 00:34:32,060
No. I sang out of tune just now.

712
00:34:32,580 --> 00:34:32,980
Drink up.

713
00:34:34,410 --> 00:34:35,330
You're finally here.

714
00:34:35,660 --> 00:34:37,250
RF's professional singer is here!

715
00:34:37,660 --> 00:34:38,020
Welcome!

716
00:34:38,620 --> 00:34:39,590
Let's welcome Mr. Shen.

717
00:34:40,060 --> 00:34:40,760
Welcome, Mr. Shen.

718
00:34:42,140 --> 00:34:42,850
Where's Dr. Qin?

719
00:34:43,410 --> 00:34:45,410
I thought we were going
to discuss the research.

720
00:34:45,450 --> 00:34:46,410
Dr. Qin?

721
00:34:46,460 --> 00:34:48,300
You would never come
if I didn't tell you that.

722
00:34:48,330 --> 00:34:50,290
This is a fine hour.
Stop talking about research.

723
00:34:50,410 --> 00:34:52,810
Life is short.
We should enjoy it while we can.

724
00:34:52,810 --> 00:34:54,580
Come on. Pour Mr. Shen some liquor.

725
00:34:54,730 --> 00:34:55,160
Mr. Shen.

726
00:34:56,180 --> 00:34:57,290
Ice, it's your song.

727
00:34:57,290 --> 00:34:58,700
Sit down.

728
00:35:02,180 --> 00:35:03,930
This is actually a song for my mother.

729
00:35:20,330 --> 00:35:25,370
♪The silver boat swaying and arching♪

730
00:35:25,700 --> 00:35:29,290
♪In the soft velvety sky♪

731
00:35:30,930 --> 00:35:36,290
♪Your disarrayed thoughts,
filled with melancholy♪

732
00:35:36,500 --> 00:35:40,580
♪Rest upon my sorrowful heart♪

733
00:35:42,180 --> 00:35:47,250
♪You say how can one not feel lonely
when love runs deep♪

734
00:35:47,890 --> 00:35:52,450
♪Consumed by emotions
when love runs deep♪

735
00:35:52,730 --> 00:35:57,980
♪My lonely and scattered emotions♪

736
00:35:58,220 --> 00:36:00,890
♪Provoke a deep sense of melancholy♪

737
00:36:01,980 --> 00:36:02,660
Mr. Shen.

738
00:36:08,620 --> 00:36:13,660
♪As if entering a new, endless season♪

739
00:36:13,930 --> 00:36:16,330
♪Day and night have fallen into disorder♪

740
00:36:16,700 --> 00:36:19,180
♪The tides rise and fall on their own whim♪

741
00:36:19,330 --> 00:36:23,770
♪There is no spring in this world♪

742
00:36:24,700 --> 00:36:29,980
♪The one who leaves wastes their tears♪

743
00:36:30,180 --> 00:36:35,410
♪Avoiding the farewell right in front of us♪

744
00:36:35,580 --> 00:36:37,980
♪You dare not think of tomorrow♪

745
00:36:38,220 --> 00:36:40,730
♪I won't say goodbye♪

746
00:36:40,980 --> 00:36:43,370
♪Some say that with every farewell♪

747
00:36:43,370 --> 00:36:50,290
♪A star in the sky fades out♪

748
00:36:51,500 --> 00:36:52,850
Excellent!

749
00:36:53,250 --> 00:36:53,850
That was nice.

750
00:36:55,540 --> 00:36:56,660
You guys sang amazingly.

751
00:36:56,930 --> 00:36:58,020
You two are something else.

752
00:36:58,450 --> 00:36:58,980
Come.

753
00:37:04,890 --> 00:37:10,020
♪The one who leaves wastes their tears♪

754
00:37:10,330 --> 00:37:15,580
♪Avoiding the farewell right in front of us♪

755
00:37:15,770 --> 00:37:18,020
♪You dare not think of tomorrow♪

756
00:37:18,450 --> 00:37:20,850
♪I won't say goodbye♪

757
00:37:21,180 --> 00:37:23,450
♪Some say that with every farewell♪

758
00:37:23,450 --> 00:37:30,410
♪A star in the sky fades out♪

759
00:37:31,370 --> 00:37:32,080
I feel terrible.

760
00:37:33,290 --> 00:37:35,810
My father-in-law finally
found his kindred spirit.

761
00:37:36,100 --> 00:37:36,680
But in the end,

762
00:37:37,100 --> 00:37:38,140
she has a terminal disease.

763
00:37:39,200 --> 00:37:40,449
What should you guys do, then?

764
00:37:40,450 --> 00:37:41,330
I have no idea.

765
00:37:42,620 --> 00:37:43,330
He wants

766
00:37:43,330 --> 00:37:45,100
to move to a nursing home
together with her.

767
00:37:45,730 --> 00:37:47,249
Shen Qing and I argued because of that.

768
00:37:47,250 --> 00:37:48,300
Shen Qing went for a jog.

769
00:37:48,730 --> 00:37:50,620
Why did you argue with him, then?

770
00:37:52,810 --> 00:37:54,280
Shen Qing feels sorry for his father.

771
00:37:54,370 --> 00:37:55,060
According to him,

772
00:37:55,370 --> 00:37:57,450
his father shouldn't stay there
together with her.

773
00:37:57,810 --> 00:37:58,900
He can visit her every day.

774
00:37:59,810 --> 00:38:00,730
Every day, you know?

775
00:38:01,100 --> 00:38:02,620
Who'll send him there and pick him up?

776
00:38:02,850 --> 00:38:04,830
He's always busy. I have
to fetch my father-in-law.

777
00:38:05,660 --> 00:38:07,660
I have to send both
his father and his son.

778
00:38:08,370 --> 00:38:09,180
Doesn't that make me

779
00:38:09,180 --> 00:38:11,250
a free chauffeur?

780
00:38:12,770 --> 00:38:14,660
You're full of anguish and complaints.

781
00:38:14,660 --> 00:38:16,730
I would've gone for a jog as well
if I were Shen Qing.

782
00:38:18,180 --> 00:38:19,370
I'm in my prime, you know?

783
00:38:19,770 --> 00:38:21,660
But my husband never comes home early.

784
00:38:21,780 --> 00:38:23,689
Although the old madam
has a terminal disease,

785
00:38:23,690 --> 00:38:26,289
my father-in-law is still willing
to spend time with her, you know?

786
00:38:26,290 --> 00:38:28,580
That old madam is outstanding indeed.

787
00:38:28,810 --> 00:38:30,540
You should learn from your elders.

788
00:38:31,140 --> 00:38:32,220
Why should I learn from her?

789
00:38:32,290 --> 00:38:33,960
Why can't Shen Qing
learn from his father?

790
00:38:34,540 --> 00:38:36,500
Shen Qing's father
was an old baby, you know?

791
00:38:36,580 --> 00:38:38,619
He only became a love saint
after his wife's passing.

792
00:38:38,620 --> 00:38:40,360
What do you want Shen Qing
to learn from him?

793
00:38:40,660 --> 00:38:43,020
Does that mean he'll only learn
after he changes his wife?

794
00:38:44,020 --> 00:38:45,530
If so, I'll live for as long as I can

795
00:38:45,570 --> 00:38:47,700
to stop Shen Qing
from taking after his father's steps.

796
00:38:48,330 --> 00:38:50,700
Liu Lina, you're something else.

797
00:38:51,100 --> 00:38:52,500
You're truly ruthless.

798
00:38:53,290 --> 00:38:54,730
My husband is never home.

799
00:38:55,730 --> 00:38:57,890
My father-in-law wants to live
in a nursing home.

800
00:38:58,290 --> 00:39:00,770
My son wants to study abroad.

801
00:39:01,930 --> 00:39:04,180
All of them want to leave the house.

802
00:39:06,180 --> 00:39:07,790
Do they think
I don't know how to do that?

803
00:39:08,020 --> 00:39:09,220
I'll leave the house as well.

804
00:39:10,700 --> 00:39:11,250
Alright!

805
00:39:12,250 --> 00:39:13,180
Don't go back tonight.

806
00:39:13,580 --> 00:39:14,290
Make them panic.

807
00:39:14,580 --> 00:39:14,930
Sure.

808
00:39:15,620 --> 00:39:16,450
Come with me tonight.

809
00:39:16,620 --> 00:39:18,219
I have plenty of spare rooms
in my house.

810
00:39:18,220 --> 00:39:18,640
Let's go.

811
00:39:19,020 --> 00:39:19,980
Cheers.

812
00:39:34,220 --> 00:39:35,250
Mom, where are you?

813
00:39:38,580 --> 00:39:39,630
I'll be back in a second.

814
00:39:39,660 --> 00:39:41,160
Go to sleep first. Don't wait for me.

815
00:39:41,700 --> 00:39:42,690
What do you mean by that?

816
00:39:42,980 --> 00:39:44,160
You're going back, aren't you?

817
00:39:44,580 --> 00:39:46,850
No one's sending Duole
to school tomorrow.

818
00:39:47,850 --> 00:39:49,330
Duole has grown up, you know?

819
00:39:49,330 --> 00:39:50,850
Can't he go to school himself?

820
00:39:51,100 --> 00:39:53,500
There are no direct buses
to their school entrance.

821
00:39:59,250 --> 00:39:59,860
Enough already.

822
00:40:00,330 --> 00:40:02,100
A carefree woman like you
will never understand

823
00:40:02,100 --> 00:40:03,909
people like us
who are attached to our children.

824
00:40:03,910 --> 00:40:04,260
See you.

825
00:40:04,660 --> 00:40:05,280
Are you leaving?

826
00:40:14,810 --> 00:40:16,580
You better stop nagging them
when you get back.

827
00:40:40,060 --> 00:40:42,020
One shredded chicken porridge to go.

828
00:40:42,580 --> 00:40:44,150
Alright. One shredded chicken porridge.

